Package net.creativeparkour

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CPMap
    Represents a CreativeParkour map, with all its properties.
    CPPlayerPosition
    Represents a player location in a parkour map, plus whether or not they are sneaking, wearing Elytra and holding EnderPearls at this location.
    CPRequest
    Used by CreativeParkour to interact with creativeparkour.net.
    CPTime
    Represents a player's performance in a particular parkour map.
    CPUtils
    Contains many simple but useful methods used in CreativeParkour.
    CPVaultUtils
    Contains useful methods related to the Vault API.
    CreativeParkour
    Main CreativeParkour class, nothing useful here for the API.
    CreativeParkourAPI
    Main CreativeParkour API class, everything starts here!
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CPMapState
    State of a CreativeParkour map.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CPRequest.InvalidQueryResponseException
    Thrown when trying to call a query response method without creating and running the Request before.
    CreativeParkourAPI.UnloadedPluginException
    Thrown when trying to use CreativeParkour's API if it is not loaded (CreativeParkour loads after most of other plugins, you should not try to access this API on server start).
